    end

    subgraph COPILOT["GitHub Copilot CLI (dot_copilot/)"]
        COP["settings.json (effortLevel xhigh · keepAlive busy · autoUpdate false · banner never<br/>+ subagents.agents review controller/lanes: gpt-5.5 xhigh, claude-opus-4.8 xhigh, PR necessity, findings/live-ui review)<br/>SessionStart/PostToolUse use shared ~/.agents/hooks; no PreToolUse shell gate<br/>symlink_copilot-instructions.md → ~/AGENTS.md · symlink_skills → ~/.agents/skills<br/>exact_agents/ review .agent.md profiles → ~/.copilot/agents/<br/>hook 07-merge-copilot-config (mcp-config.json 0600 + hooks/agent-memory.json write;<br/>settings.json jq deep-merge over Copilot's runtime-owned file)<br/>,copilot launcher: refresh header-auth MCP tokens (,mcp-token --login, no-op if fresh) + re-bake mcp-config.json via generator, then native Copilot<br/>,copilot-cloudflare / ,copilot-openrouter set Copilot BYOK env then exec ,copilot<br/>MCP: stdio→type local · own OAuth http unused (redirect 127.0.0.1:{port}/ unregistered)<br/>slack + scsi-main→headers.Authorization via $(,mcp-token &lt;server&gt; --bearer) (ride cursor's rotating tokens; Copilot can't run Slack/Okta OAuth; opaque tokens use ~/.cache/mcp-token refresh ledger)<br/>scsi-local→type local (stdio, pass creds); headroom excluded for Copilot → mcpServers = slack + scsi-main + scsi-local (+ built-ins)"]:::cop
    end

